title: US on brink of government shutdown after Senate rejects funding plans
summary: The Senate failed to pass proposals from both Democrats and Republicans to extend government funding and prevent a shutdown after midnight. As a result, the government faces the possibility of a shutdown due to a lack of agreement on budget measures. Lawmakers continue to negotiate, but time is running out to reach a resolution.
